+  // <---- lower bound -----> <----------- succ -------------> <---- upper bound ----->
+  // [min_int .. lo_type->hi] [lo_type->hi+1 .. hi_type->lo-1] [hi_type->lo .. max_int]
+  //                         ^                                ^
+  //                     n {>/>=} lo                      n {</<=} hi
+  //
+  // The trick is then to "shift down" the succ range, to create only
+  // a single transition point.
